        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 1:22PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 119 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cuchara Pass, or 25 miles west of Trinidad, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Locally heavy rain and gusty winds

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Heavy rains may cause streams on the south slopes of the
Spanish Peak to run high. Flash flooding could occur.

Locations impacted include...
South and east slopes of Spanish Peaks.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, be alert for quickly rising streams in the Spanish
Creek region.</instruction>
